The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 December is 15,696 (1,816.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 December, there were 2,832 new confirmed cases (327.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 December, there were 1,600 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 77% (1,232 extra cases).
